{
  "stem": "12768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But my older brother already had too many kids, so they didn't want him to volunteer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So we were three brothers in the army at the same time, my brother Paul and my brother Harry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But they went different battalions, because they volunteered at different times, after me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I'm the first one in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they first came in in early '45.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And so in April of '45, we knew-- we had heard on the radio that Prince Bernadotte and the Danish Red Cross and Danish offers and buses that was painted white have gone to Germany.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The Swedish prince had negotiated with Himmler of-- that all Scandinavian prisoners should be returned to the country of origins.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And at that time, Germany had already started falling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So they made a deal with Himmler.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the buses were sent out of Denmark-- that was in April of 1945-- to Germany and into Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And they came to the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And my mother didn't know it, maybe, till an hour before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They wondered what those buses were come into the city for.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they were told to pack all their things, or take the least with them as possible.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But boarded the buses, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "My mother took-- she had been working as-- as a maid, as a cleaner woman, as a-- stacking books and all-- and other things from other prisoners that had come into the camp.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They had come in, and it was like they was there maybe a couple of days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then the Germans again sent them on cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And there was Eastern Europe's Jews, you know, that came in, Italian Jews, wherever they came from, into this camp of Therisienstadt.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
